To generate a table of contents (TOC) automatically in a LATEX document, follow these steps:

1. Ensure that you have a document class that supports a TOC, such as `article`, `report`, or `book`.
2. Insert the `\usepackage{tocloft}` package at the beginning of your document.
3. Use the `\renewcommand{\cfttoctitlefont}{\hfill\bfseries}` command to customize the appearance of the TOC title.
4. Use the `\renewcommand{\cftsecfont}{\normalfont\itshape}` command to change the font of the section headings in the TOC.
5. Use the `\renewcommand{\cftsecafterpnum}{\hfill\parindent10pt}` command to add a one-line indentation after each TOC entry's page number.
6. Use the `\setcounter{tocdepth}{2}` command to limit the depth of the TOC to two levels.

Example:

```
\documentclass{article}
\usepackage{tocloft}

\renewcommand{\cfttoctitlefont}{\hfill\bfseries}
\renewcommand{\cftsecfont}{\normalfont\itshape}
\renewcommand{\cftsecafterpnum}{\hfill\parindent10pt}
\setcounter{tocdepth}{2}

\begin{document}

\tableofcontents

\section{Introduction}
\subsection{Background}
\subsection{Purpose}

\section{Methods}
\subsection{Data Collection}
\subsection{Data Analysis}

\section{Results}
\subsection{Descriptive Statistics}
\subsection{Inferential Statistics}

\section{Discussion}
\subsection{Implications}
\subsection{Limitations}

\end{document}
```

In this example, the `\renewcommand` commands are used to customize the appearance of the TOC title, section headings, and section numbers in the TOC. The `\setcounter{tocdepth}{2}` command limits the depth of the TOC to two levels. The result is a properly formatted TOC that lists the main sections and subsections of the document.

